# UI: shadcn/ui + brand theme

## Component strategy (order)

1. **Reuse** existing shadcn primitives under `@/components/ui` (see `components.json` aliases).
2. **If missing** and it exists in the shadcn registry, add it with the CLI: `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component>` (or `npx shadcn@latest add <component>`), aligned with `components.json` and `app/globals.css`.
3. **If there is no shadcn component** (nothing to `add`) or a one-off is enough: **implement the UI inline** in the same file (or page/feature file) with React + Tailwind + theme tokens. **Do not** create new shared components under `components/` for small, single-use markup—avoid unnecessary abstraction and extra files.

When something is reused **many times** across routes or grows real state/behavior, then extract a component—but default to inline for simple, one-off UI.

## Brand theme — `app/globals.css` is source of truth

- **Do not** introduce one-off hex/HSL or random Tailwind palette colors for product UI.
- **Do** use semantic tokens wired to CSS variables: e.g. `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-card`, `text-card-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`, `bg-secondary`, `text-secondary-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `ring-ring`, radii like `rounded-lg` / `rounded-xl` that map to `--radius`, typography like `font-heading` where appropriate.
- Light/dark: respect `.dark` and existing variables in `:root` / `.dark` — extend the theme **in `globals.css`** when new tokens are needed, then consume via utilities or `@theme inline` mappings already there.

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ No shadcn primitive: keep markup in the page/feature file
<section className="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-accent/80 px-4 py-4">...</section>

// ✅ Use shadcn + theme tokens
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
;<Button variant="default">Save</Button>
<div className="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-6 text-card-foreground">

// ❌ Avoid ad-hoc colors
<div className="bg-[#1a1a1a] text-gray-200">
```

When composing new patterns, mirror shadcn’s Radix + `cn()` patterns and `class-variance-authority` variants already used in `@/components/ui`.
